table.name: ship_unit
table.description: This table stores the unit level information at the order release level. It is a parallel table to S_SHIP_UNIT table (at the Shipment level).

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_GID
columns.description: The GID for the ship unit associated to an order release.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_XID
columns.description: The XID for the ship unit associated to a order release.

columns.name: IS_SPLITABLE
columns.description: A Y/N flag to identify if the ship unit can be split when creating an order.

columns.name: TRANSPORT_HANDLING_UNIT_GID
columns.description: The transport handling unit identifier defined for the ship unit. Examples are a box and a pallet.

columns.name: UNIT_LENGTH
columns.description: The length of each order release ship unit. If this row represents 20 of the same ship units, the total length is 20 x unit length.

columns.name: UNIT_LENGTH_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for the unit length column.

columns.name: UNIT_LENGTH_BASE
columns.description: The unit length in base units.

columns.name: UNIT_WIDTH
columns.description: The width of each order release ship unit. Each row may represent the ship unit count number of same ship units. If this field is null or is 0, the weight of this order release ship unit is computed as the total of container weight from its ship unit specification and the weight of its shipment ship unit lines.

columns.name: UNIT_WIDTH_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for the unit width.

columns.name: UNIT_WIDTH_BASE
columns.description: The unit width in base units.

columns.name: UNIT_HEIGHT
columns.description: The height of each order release ship unit. If this row represents the 20 same ship units, the total height is 20 x unit height.

columns.name: UNIT_HEIGHT_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for unit height column.

columns.name: UNIT_HEIGHT_BASE
columns.description: The unit height in base units.

columns.name: UNIT_WEIGHT
columns.description: The weight of the ship unit.

columns.name: UNIT_WEIGHT_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for the unit weight.

columns.name: UNIT_WEIGHT_BASE
columns.description: The unit weight in base units.

columns.name: UNIT_VOLUME
columns.description: The volume of each order release ship unit. Each row may represent the ship unit count number of same ship units. If this field is null or is 0, the volume of this shipment ship unit is computed as the total of container volume from its ship unit specification and the volume of its shipment ship unit lines.

columns.name: UNIT_VOLUME_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for the unit volume.

columns.name: UNIT_VOLUME_BASE
columns.description: The unit volume in base units.

columns.name: FLEX_COMMODITY_CODE
columns.description: The user defined commodity code for the item. E.g.. the HTS, NMFC, SITC, STCC codes for the item.

columns.name: FLEX_COMMODITY_QUAL_GID
columns.description: A unique identifier to define the type of the code. E.g.. HTS, SITC, STCC, NMFC etc.

columns.name: IS_SYSTEM_GENERATED
columns.description: A Y/N indicator to define if the record is generated by the system for the order base or copied (may be from XML).

columns.name: ORDER_RELEASE_GID
columns.description: The order release associated to this ship unit.

columns.name: OR_EQUIPMENT_SEQ
columns.description: Associates equipment of the order release to this particular ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_COUNT
columns.description: Ship units that have the same dimension/weight and contents are represented as one row in the SHIP_UNIT table. The ship unit count is the number of these ship units.

columns.name: OB_SHIP_UNIT_GID
columns.description: The order base ship unit associated with the order release ship unit if it was created from an order base and the releasing logic.

columns.name: UNIT_NET_WEIGHT
columns.description: The net weight of the ship unit.

columns.name: UNIT_NET_WEIGHT_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for the unit net weight.

columns.name: UNIT_NET_WEIGHT_BASE
columns.description: The unit net weight in base units.

columns.name: UNIT_NET_VOLUME
columns.description: The net volume of the ship unit.

columns.name: UNIT_NET_VOLUME_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for the unit net volume.

columns.name: UNIT_NET_VOLUME_BASE
columns.description: The unit net volume in base units.

columns.name: SECONDARY_UNIT_WEIGHT
columns.description: An additional value for the secondary gross weight of the ship unit.

columns.name: SECONDARY_UNIT_WEIGHT_UOM_CODE
columns.description: Unit of measure for secondary weight column.

columns.name: SECONDARY_UNIT_WEIGHT_BASE
columns.description: The secondary weight in base units.

columns.name: SECONDARY_UNIT_VOLUME
columns.description: An additional value for the secondary gross volume of the ship unit.

columns.name: SECONDARY_UNIT_VOLUME_UOM_CODE
columns.description: Unit of measure for the secondary volume.

columns.name: SECONDARY_UNIT_VOLUME_BASE
columns.description: The secondary volume in base units.

columns.name: SECONDRY_UNIT_NET_WT
columns.description: An additional value for the secondary net weight of the ship unit.

columns.name: SECONDRY_UNIT_NET_WT_UOM_CODE
columns.description: Unit of measure for secondary net weight column.

columns.name: SECONDRY_UNIT_NET_WT_BASE
columns.description: The secondary net weight in base units.

columns.name: SECONDRY_UNIT_NET_VOL
columns.description: An additional value for the secondary net volume of the ship unit.

columns.name: SECONDRY_UNIT_NET_VOL_UOM_CODE
columns.description: Unit of measure for the net secondary volume.

columns.name: SECONDRY_UNIT_NET_VOL_BASE
columns.description: The secondary net volume in base units.

columns.name: CORE_DIAMETER
columns.description: For cylindrical objects, this defines the diameter of the core

columns.name: CORE_DIAMETER_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for the diameter of the core

columns.name: CORE_DIAMETER_BASE
columns.description: The diameter of the core in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: UNIT_DIAMETER
columns.description: The unit diameter of the ship unit.

columns.name: UNIT_DIAMETER_UOM_CODE
columns.description: Unit of measure for the unit diameter.

columns.name: UNIT_DIAMETER_BASE
columns.description: The unit diameter in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: TAG_1
columns.description: A flexible field to contain informational data that has been copied from the order to the shipment.

columns.name: TAG_2
columns.description: A flexible field to contain informational data that has been copied from the order to the shipment.

columns.name: TAG_3
columns.description: A flexible field to contain informational data that has been copied from the order to the shipment.

columns.name: TAG_4
columns.description: A flexible field to contain informational data that has been copied from the order to the shipment.

columns.name: OB_SU_RELEASE_INSTR_SEQ
columns.description: The release instruction associated to the order base if the order release was created from an order base through the releasing logic.

columns.name: IS_COUNT_SPLITTABLE
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether the ship unit can be split on the count boundaries when planning during container optimization.

columns.name: PICKUP_OR_STOP_GID
columns.description: This ship unit is going to be picked up at this stop. If this field is empty, this ship unit is picked up at the order's source location.

columns.name: DROPOFF_OR_STOP_GID
columns.description: This ship unit is going to be dropped off at this stop. If this field is empty, this ship unit is dropped off at the order's destination location.

columns.name: DOMAIN_NAME
columns.description: Database domain where this data is stored.

columns.name: INSERT_USER
columns.description: The user ID of the data insert user.

columns.name: INSERT_DATE
columns.description: Date and time of data insert.

columns.name: UPDATE_USER
columns.description: The user ID of the data update user.

columns.name: UPDATE_DATE
columns.description: Date and time of the most recent data update.

columns.name: TOTAL_GROSS_WEIGHT
columns.description: The total gross weight of the order release ship unit (transport handling unit + lines).

columns.name: TOTAL_GROSS_WEIGHT_BASE
columns.description: The total gross weight unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_GROSS_WEIGHT_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The total gross weight in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_GROSS_VOLUME
columns.description: The total gross volume of the order release ship unit (transport handling unit + lines).

columns.name: TOTAL_GROSS_VOLUME_BASE
columns.description: The total gross volume unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_GROSS_VOLUME_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The total gross volume in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: LOAD_CONFIG_SETUP_GID
columns.description: A load configurator set up identifier to be used by the load configuration engine as the input rules for how the ship unit was built.

columns.name: IS_ALLOW_REPACK
columns.description: A Y/N field, if this flag is set to false, when planning order movement that contains this shipment ship unit or combine shipments that contains this shipment ship unit, the shipment ship unit building process will not repack this s ship unit.
